title: For Trade:  franchi 12 gauge - black magic game.
postcontent:
Very nice gun, awesome condition.  the stock had a hairline crack in it, had it stripped and fixed, then refinished.  very nice dark wood stain.  it is gas operated semi auto, very easy to take apart and clean.  gold trigger and trim in great condition. 3" chamber, chrome-moly ribbed barrel.  i just have zero use for it as i am not a shotgun guy by any means. 

you cannot find this gun for sale anymore.  there are a coupe fake auction sites out there that say they have sold these for 366.00 but that is 100% not true and they say that about everygun to lure you to the site.  please base prices off of gunbroker.com  that is the only acurate site if you must base off of an auction site.  these sold for $600+ when they were in stores.

the reason they are not sold anymore... gas operated shotguns will cycle through any shell clean.  most semi auto shotguns are inertia based and will only cycle through when enough inertia is made from the load.  gas ones cost too much to make when people didnt know the difference between gas and inertia.  so they decided to make 12g models that werent gas and discontinued the gas ones.  still easy to find parts for online, not that you'll need them.

title: For Sale:  ASAI One Pro
postcontent: Designed by Martin Tuma for Advanced Small Arms Industries (ASAI) in Solothurn, Switzerland, it is manufactured by Oerlikon in Zurich, Switzerland and imported by Magnum Research of Minneapolis, Minnesota. Roughly 1000 of these Swiss made ASAI One Pro .45's were imported by Magnum Research in either .45 ACP or .400 Corbon which makes them extreme;y rare to find, let alone in LNIB condition. Firearm is in excellent 98%+ condition (serial #022XX). Both of the original 10 round magazines are included in addition to a third. Aimed initially at meeting the demanding requirements of Special Operations Command units, the One Pro 45 pistol will no doubt find favor with civilian fans of “big-bore” double action semi-automatic pistols. The One Pro 45 combines proven short-recoil operation, all-steel construction and large caliber with a modern single-action/double action trigger, a frame mounted decocking lever and a patented, automatic firing pin safety. Accuracy and service life are enhanced by the full length rails—interior on the frame and exterior on the slide—and the slide and frame of chromium nickel- molybdenum steel. Out of the box, the One Pro 45 offers one of the best trigger pulls for a factory pistol. Single-action pulls are light and crisp with very little slack or creep. Double-action pulls are of moderate weight with linear loading and a predictable, crisp let-off. No doubt accuracy is greatly enhanced by the excellent qualities of the trigger. ASAI claims that the One Pro 45 will find favor among shooters with small hands. Despite the double-column magazine, the girth of the grip frame remains comfortable for the small handed. Shooting comfort is enhanced by a slight recurve at the bottom of the grip frame and recurved magazine floorplate extensions. Stocks are two-piece molded, black polymer with a lightly marbled outer surface. Caliber: .45 ACP/AUTO Capacity: (3) 10 Round Magazines Sights: 3- Contrast Barrel Length: 3 6/8" Weight: 2.55 Lbs Shipping to lower 48 only, Shipping $30.00 For more detailed information on the One Pro see the following link to a 1998 NRA review: http://www.nramuseum.org/media/364163/June%2098.pdf. With only about 1,000 imported to the US, this is indeed a rare find (serial #022XX) in what appears to be 98% condition.
